622
00:27:58,081 --> 00:28:00,082
(indistinct chatter, crying)

623
00:28:08,316 --> 00:28:10,751
(school bell ringing)

624
00:28:13,054 --> 00:28:15,455
(spray can shaking)

625
00:28:25,266 --> 00:28:27,968
(indistinct,
overlapping chatter)

626
00:28:28,002 --> 00:28:29,669
(high-pitched squeaking)

627
00:28:30,671 --> 00:28:31,938
(beep)

628
00:28:31,973 --> 00:28:33,640
Seriously?

629
00:28:33,674 --> 00:28:34,975
(beep)

630
00:28:35,009 --> 00:28:36,910
(high-pitched squeaking)

631
00:28:36,944 --> 00:28:39,412
SUE: At the risk of
stepping out of character,

632
00:28:39,447 --> 00:28:42,249
I brought donuts to calm
everyone's frayed nerves,

633
00:28:42,283 --> 00:28:44,618
until some rent-a-cop
put his greasy palm prints

634
00:28:44,652 --> 00:28:46,052
all over my French crullers.

635
00:28:46,087 --> 00:28:47,788
Hmm. I don't mind.

636
00:28:47,822 --> 00:28:49,890
I'll never forget
the look on their faces

637
00:28:49,924 --> 00:28:51,825
when that gun went off.

638
00:28:51,859 --> 00:28:53,894
Something was taken from them...

639
00:28:53,928 --> 00:28:57,063
their innocence, their idealism,

640
00:28:57,098 --> 00:28:58,298
their feeling of safety.

641
00:28:58,332 --> 00:28:59,800
BEISTE:
I just hope we get

642
00:28:59,834 --> 00:29:01,034
the students back.

643
00:29:01,068 --> 00:29:03,403
Half of them didn't
even show up today.

644
00:29:03,437 --> 00:29:05,238
Oh, my goodness,
I haven't seen this

645
00:29:05,273 --> 00:29:06,640
level of overreaction

646
00:29:06,674 --> 00:29:09,810
since Janet Jackson showed her
saggy fun bag at the Super Bowl.

647
00:29:09,844 --> 00:29:12,145
What if it wasn't even a gun?

648
00:29:12,180 --> 00:29:14,815
You ever think about that?
Cops didn't find one.

649
00:29:14,849 --> 00:29:15,816
It could just as easily
have been firecrackers,

650
00:29:15,850 --> 00:29:16,983
or a car backfiring.

651
00:29:17,018 --> 00:29:18,151
I grew up on a farm,

652
00:29:18,186 --> 00:29:20,086
and I know what
a gunshot sounds like.

653
00:29:20,121 --> 00:29:21,321
Somebody fired

654
00:29:21,355 --> 00:29:22,489
a gun in this school.

655
00:29:22,523 --> 00:29:25,091
And quite frankly,
I don't feel safe

656
00:29:25,126 --> 00:29:26,893
knowing there's some kid
with a gun

657
00:29:26,928 --> 00:29:28,829
stuffed in his backpack
walking around these halls.

658
00:29:28,863 --> 00:29:30,730
No. Either the kid
took the gun home,

659
00:29:30,765 --> 00:29:33,333
in which case, they won't
be able to bring it back

660
00:29:33,367 --> 00:29:34,801
because of the new
metal detectors.

661
00:29:34,836 --> 00:29:36,236
Or the kid stashed it somewhere

662
00:29:36,270 --> 00:29:37,504
here at school.
Yeah.

663
00:29:37,538 --> 00:29:40,073
In which case, the police
are going to find it.

664
00:29:40,107 --> 00:29:41,942
I mean, they are
searching every locker,

665
00:29:41,976 --> 00:29:43,677
and interviewing
every single student.

666
00:29:43,711 --> 00:29:45,512
Every single student?

667
00:29:45,546 --> 00:29:49,015
Yeah. Then when they find
who did it, the kid's

668
00:29:49,050 --> 00:29:51,051
going to be expelled.

669
00:29:53,287 --> 00:29:56,189
Well, no student's
going to get expelled.

670
00:29:56,224 --> 00:29:58,191
BEISTE:
Why not?

671
00:29:58,226 --> 00:30:00,227
'Cause it was my gun.

672
00:30:08,469 --> 00:30:10,437
(school bell ringing)

673
00:30:10,471 --> 00:30:12,005
It's registered.

674
00:30:12,039 --> 00:30:13,540
I have a license for it.

675
00:30:13,574 --> 00:30:15,508
I'm sorry,
but in light of recent events,

676
00:30:15,543 --> 00:30:17,677
I feel more safe
with it in my office.

677
00:30:17,712 --> 00:30:19,946
Look, Sue, I'm not going
to argue the merits

678
00:30:19,981 --> 00:30:21,781
of armed teachers right now.

679
00:30:21,816 --> 00:30:24,217
It's a different world from
when you and I started teaching.

680
00:30:24,252 --> 00:30:25,552
Or rather,
when I started teaching,

681
00:30:25,586 --> 00:30:27,587
and you started doing
whatever it is that you do.

682
00:30:27,622 --> 00:30:28,755
The safety net

683
00:30:28,789 --> 00:30:32,259
of the public
mental health system is gone.

684
00:30:32,293 --> 00:30:35,095
Parents with troubled kids
are too busy working three jobs

685
00:30:35,129 --> 00:30:36,763
to look after them,

686
00:30:36,797 --> 00:30:39,900
and the gun yahoos
have everyone so worked up

687
00:30:39,934 --> 00:30:41,835
about Obama
taking away their guns

688
00:30:41,869 --> 00:30:44,905
that every house has
a readily-available arsenal.

689
00:30:44,939 --> 00:30:47,440
But having a gun
to make you feel safe,

690
00:30:47,475 --> 00:30:51,444
and shooting it in school
are two different things.

691
00:30:51,479 --> 00:30:53,246
I was just doing my daily

692
00:30:53,281 --> 00:30:55,615
<i>safety check,</i>
<i>making sure Uma Thurman...</i>

693
00:30:55,650 --> 00:30:57,517
<i>that's what I call her...</i>

694
00:30:57,551 --> 00:31:00,754
<i>was locked up tight, and</i>
<i>she accidentally went off.</i>

695
00:31:00,788 --> 00:31:04,124
When she fired, I dropped her,

696
00:31:04,158 --> 00:31:07,260
and the second shot came
when the gun hit the floor.

697
00:31:07,295 --> 00:31:08,862
This doesn't make
any sense, Sue.

698
00:31:08,896 --> 00:31:11,798
Bullets leave bullet marks,
shell casings.

699
00:31:11,832 --> 00:31:13,934
The casings are at
the bottom of a lake.

700
00:31:13,968 --> 00:31:16,937
And I moved some posters
and a tub of protein powder

701
00:31:16,971 --> 00:31:18,571
to cover up the holes.

702
00:31:18,606 --> 00:31:20,640
"Cover-up" is
the optimal phrase.

703
00:31:20,675 --> 00:31:22,709
I panicked.

704
00:31:22,743 --> 00:31:25,111
Okay? I'm...

705
00:31:25,146 --> 00:31:27,113
I'm sorry.

706
00:31:27,148 --> 00:31:28,448
It took a couple

707
00:31:28,482 --> 00:31:31,084
of days for me
to come to my senses,

708
00:31:31,118 --> 00:31:35,355
but I'm here now,
ready to take my punishment.

709
00:31:38,859 --> 00:31:41,795
You do realize
my hands are tied, don't you?

710
00:31:41,829 --> 00:31:44,798
I have to report to the police
and the school board.

711
00:31:44,832 --> 00:31:47,801
There are policies
in place, Sue.

712
00:31:47,835 --> 00:31:49,903
Zero tolerance policies.

713
00:31:49,937 --> 00:31:52,372
Yeah, I'm aware of them.

714
00:31:54,342 --> 00:31:57,143
You know, it's funny
how this stuff works out.

715
00:31:57,178 --> 00:32:00,513
An entire career doing
the right thing, winning.

716
00:32:02,850 --> 00:32:05,618
I sent Cheerios off
to the Ivy Leagues.

717
00:32:05,653 --> 00:32:08,088
I educated girls who are CEOs

718
00:32:08,122 --> 00:32:10,390
of Fortune 500 companies.

719
00:32:10,424 --> 00:32:13,093
They're mothers,
gold medalists.

720
00:32:13,127 --> 00:32:15,095
I've coached two Grammy winners,

721
00:32:15,129 --> 00:32:17,097
an Internet billionaire

722
00:32:17,131 --> 00:32:20,133
and a lesbian
secretary of state.

723
00:32:23,604 --> 00:32:27,307
But all I'll be remembered for

724
00:32:27,341 --> 00:32:29,442
is this one thing.

725
00:32:33,547 --> 00:32:35,782
It'll be the first line
of my obituary.

726
00:32:36,851 --> 00:32:39,786
I'm sorry, Sue.

727
00:32:39,820 --> 00:32:42,188
I have no choice.

728
00:32:55,489 --> 00:32:59,422
BLAINE: I couldn't sleep,
neither could my mom and dad,

729
00:32:59,456 --> 00:33:02,492
so we just stayed up
all night, talking

730
00:33:02,526 --> 00:33:04,460
and crying
and hugging each other.

731
00:33:04,495 --> 00:33:05,928
I know.

732
00:33:05,963 --> 00:33:08,131
My parents wanted me
to stay home this week,

733
00:33:08,165 --> 00:33:10,333
but I told them, no way.

734
00:33:13,570 --> 00:33:15,104
It sounds crazy,
Blaine, but I...

735
00:33:15,139 --> 00:33:18,007
I wanted to be in that
choir room with you guys.

736
00:33:18,042 --> 00:33:19,342
Believe me, you didn't.

737
00:33:19,376 --> 00:33:20,826
It was the most scared I think
I've ever been in my life.

738
00:33:20,843 --> 00:33:23,144
Me, too, but not because
of what was happening,

739
00:33:23,178 --> 00:33:24,912
but because I
couldn't get to you,

740
00:33:24,947 --> 00:33:27,115
or do anything
to help you, or...

741
00:33:27,149 --> 00:33:29,984
(sighs)

742
00:33:30,018 --> 00:33:32,053
(voice breaking):
Or even say good-bye.

743
00:33:32,087 --> 00:33:35,823
I-I think the important thing is
that no one got hurt.

744
00:33:35,858 --> 00:33:37,925
Yeah. (Sniffles)

745
00:33:37,960 --> 00:33:40,328
And that you know
that you're my family.

746
00:33:40,362 --> 00:33:41,662
(sniffles)

747
00:33:41,697 --> 00:33:43,965
Everybody in that room
is my family.

748
00:33:43,999 --> 00:33:46,968
And I didn't want the
last thing you guys heard

749
00:33:47,002 --> 00:33:49,837
